
@startuml

' Define classes based on the requirement

class Location {
  +String name
  +int capacity
  +List<Exhibition> exhibitions
}

class Exhibition {
  +String title
  +Date startDate
  +Date endDate
  +Location location
  +Employee coordinator
  +List<ExhibitionItem> items
}

class Employee {
  +String name
  +String role
  +Employee coach
  +List<Exhibition> exhibitionsCoordinated
  +List<Employee> juniorEmployees
}

class ExhibitionItem {
  +String description
  +String category
  +List<Piece> requestedPieces
  +Exhibition exhibition
}

class Piece {
  +String title
  +Artist artist
  +Collector collector
  +ExhibitionItem item
}

class Artist {
  +String name
  +Date birthDate
  +Date deathDate
}

class Collector {
  +String name
  +String contactInfo
  +List<Piece> ownedPieces
}

' Relationships

' A Location has multiple Exhibitions
Location "1" -- "*" Exhibition : contains

' An Exhibition is coordinated by one Employee
Exhibition "1" -- "1" Employee : coordinated by

' An Exhibition consists of multiple ExhibitionItems
Exhibition "1" -- "*" ExhibitionItem : includes

' An ExhibitionItem may have multiple Pieces
ExhibitionItem "1" -- "*" Piece : requests

' A Piece belongs to one Artist and one Collector
Piece "1" -- "1" Artist : created by
Piece "1" -- "1" Collector : owned by

' An Employee may have a Coach (Senior Employee)
Employee "1" -- "0..1" Employee : coached by
Employee "1" -- "*" Employee : coaches

' A Collector owns multiple Pieces
Collector "1" -- "*" Piece : owns

@enduml

---

### 📌 Explanation of Key Elements:

- **`Location`**: Represents a part of the museum that can host exhibitions.
- **`Exhibition`**: A specific event planned in a `Location`, managed by an `Employee`.
- **`ExhibitionItem`**: A specific item or theme within an exhibition, e.g., "A sunflower painting".
- **`Piece`**: A physical artwork (e.g., Van Gogh's *Sunflowers*), sourced from a `Collector`.
- **`Artist`**: The creator of the piece.
- **`Collector`**: Owns one or more pieces and can be contacted for loaning them.
- **`Employee`**: Museum staff who coordinate exhibitions and may have coaching relationships.

